1. Installation Prerequisites
  a. Install Oracle/OpenJDK 8 or its predecessor.
  b. cp set_env.template set_env
  c. Modify set_env to make JXPerf_HOME and JAVA_HOME point to your JXPerf home and Java home.
  d. source set_env

2. Installation
  a. make

3. Uninstallation
  a. make clean

4. To run dead store detection
  a. LD_PRELOAD=$JXPerf_HOME/build/libpreload.so java -agentpath:$JXPerf_HOME/build/libagent.so=DeadStore::MEM_UOPS_RETIRED:ALL_STORES:precise=2@<sampling rate> -cp <classpath> <java_program>
  b. $JXPerf_HOME/process_raw_data.py
    1) A dump file named "agent-data" would be generated

5. To run silent store detection
  a. LD_PRELOAD=$JXPerf_HOME/build/libpreload.so java -agentpath:$JXPerf_HOME/build/libagent.so=SilentStore::MEM_UOPS_RETIRED:ALL_STORES:precise=2@<sampling rate> -cp <classpath> <java_program>
  b. $JXPerf_HOME/process_raw_data.py
    1) A dump file named "agent-data" would be generated

6. To run silent load detection
  a. LD_PRELOAD=$JXPerf_HOME/build/libpreload.so java -agentpath:$JXPerf_HOME/build/libagent.so=SilentLoad::MEM_UOPS_RETIRED:ALL_LOADS:precise=2@<sampling rate> -cp <classpath> <java_program>
  b. $JXPerf_HOME/process_raw_data.py
    1) A dump file named "agent-data" would be generated

7. To run data centric analysis
  a. LD_PRELOAD=$JXPerf_HOME/build/libpreload.so java -javaagent:$JAVA_AGENT -agentpath:$JXPerf_HOME/build/libagent.so=DataCentric::MEM_LOAD_UOPS_RETIRED:L1_MISS:precise=2@<sampling rate> -cp <classpath> <java_program>
  b. $JXPerf_HOME/process_raw_data.py
    1) Two dump files named "agent-allocation" and "agent-cachemiss" would be generated
      a) agent-allocation file reports allocation times for every allocation site
      b) agent-cachemiss file reports pairs of calling context (i.e., <allocation site, access site>) for data incurring L1 cache misses in descending order
      c) To analyze memory bloat
        (1) Check the agent-cachemiss file to identify the data suffering from high L1 cache misses 
	(2) Check the agent-allocation file to see whether these problematic data have high allocation times
